Run Python replications from the resolved study folder

python_run_dir() fell back to getwd() when no local sibling study folder
was found, so on a Shiny server REPLICATE_STUDY_ROOT pointed at the app
directory and scripts read data from the wrong path (e.g.
ShinyApps/replicate/data/raw/...), causing FileNotFoundError. Fall back to
ensure_study_folder_local() (the materialized GitHub clone) like Stata does,
and run the Python process with its working directory set to the study root.
